description: S'mores cookie bar recipe with instructions in only video caption
caption:
4 simple ingredients and a few minutes before this are in the oven! This is our go-to dessert we take to cookouts. Everyone loves them!

Ingredients
2-3 packages @sweetlorens chocolate chip cookie dough
2 cups chocolate chips (we used @enjoylifefoods )
1 cup crushed gluten free graham crackers or @simplemills honey sweet thins
1-2 cups marshmallow fluff

Press half of your dough in a single layer in the bottom of a parchment line square baking pan. We used about 1 1/2 packs of @sweetlorenscookie dough for this. Use your fingers to press the dough into the pan.

Sprinkle the chocolate chips evenly on top and spread them out so the cookies are almost covered in chocolate.

Crumble the graham crackers up and sprinkle them on top of the chocolate layer. The graham crackers have to be the middle layer because they won’t stick to the cookie dough.

Scoop the marshmallow fluff on top and use a spatula to spread it out into an even layer. Spray the spatula with nonstick spray before spreading if you’re having trouble with it sticking.

Press the rest of the dough flat and lay them in rows on top of the marshmallow. It’s ok if the marshmallow is showing through.

Bake them for 25-30 minutes, until the cookies are set and just golden brown. Keep a close eye on them the last 10 minutes to make sure the edges of the cookies and the marshmallow don’t burn.

Let them cool for at least an hour (ugh I know) then cut them into squares. You can speed up cooling by putting them in the fridge or freezer. #smorescookies #smoresbars #smores #summerdessert

description: Person giving advice for what to say during job interview and then acting out scenario
caption:
😩 This question is sooo tricky to answer without coming off arrogant or cocky.

🔥 But here’s my pro tip: attribute the strength to feedback or a compliment.

Instead of:
❌ “I’m extremely good at communication, it’s a gift.”
Try:
✅ “My previous managers have always noted how proactive I am when it comes to communication. While I’m an independent worker, I love to proactively give my managers updates before they feel the need to ask!”

✨ You want the interviewer to think “Wow! That’s a really important strength to have in this role. And they said it so modestly!!”

🫶🏼 Typically, you want to hit on a soft, interpersonal skill. Sure — you can say your greatest strength is photoshop, but it just ends up sounding flat.

Try picking something that’s appropriate for you industry. For example:

Video editor ➡️ collaboration
Early childhood educator ➡️ playfulness
Project manager ➡️ organization
Client lead ➡️ tine management
Nurse ➡️ compassion
Marketing coordinator ➡️ communication
911 operator ➡️ composure
#career #careeradvice #careertiktok #careertok #resume #coverletter #college #internship #jobinterview
